{{Year nav topic5|1988|chess}}
Events in [[chess]] in 1988.

==Top players==

Kasparov and Karpov remained the top two players in the world, positions that they had held since July 1982.  Over the year, [[Dutch people|Dutch]] player [[Jan Timman]] and [[Alexander Beliavsky]] of the USSR moved up the list, whilst [[Andrei Sokolov]] from the USSR and [[Ljubomir Ljubojević]] of [[Yugoslavia]] moved down.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chess.eusa.ed.ac.uk/Chess/Trivia/AlltimeList.html |title=Top men's ratings 1970–1997 |accessdate=5 August 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100724043700/http://chess.eusa.ed.ac.uk/Chess/Trivia/AlltimeList.html |archivedate=24 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

