'''Malmö SS''', ''Malmö Simsällskap'', is a Swedish swim team from [[Malmö]] founded 1869. The competitive swimming and diving ended in 1982 when an alliance with [[Limhamns SS]] called [[Malmö KK]] started, but Malmö SS still hands beginner's swimming and diving. Malmö SS most famous swimmer is two time [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] champion [[Gunnar Larsson (swimmer)|Gunnar Larsson]].

