{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = The Maer Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = Exmouth Cricket Ground - geograph.org.uk - 1091496.jpg | location = [[Exmouth, Devon|Exmouth]], [[Devon]] | establishment = 1874 | seating_capacity = | home club = Exmouth | county club = [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]] | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1874&ndash;present | club1 = [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]] | date = 2 January | year = 2009 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/473.html Ground profile }}
'''The Maer Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Exmouth, Devon|Exmouth]], [[Devon]]. It is the home ground of [[Exmouth Cricket Club]] and is also used regularly by [[Devon County Cricket Club]].
The first recorded match played on the ground was in 1874 when Devon played Will-o'-the-Wisp. From 1883 to 1889 the ground played host to eight matches between Devon and the [[Marylebone Cricket Club]]. In 1951, the Maer hosted Devon's first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match against [[Berkshire County Cricket Club|Berkshire]], and has since played host to 49 Minor Counties Championship matches. The ground played host to a Women's [[One Day International]] between [[England women's cricket team|England]] and [[New Zealand women's cricket team|New Zealand]] in the [[1973 Women's Cricket World Cup|1973 Women's World Cup]]. In 1986, it hosted its first [[List A cricket|List A]] match in the [[1986 NatWest Trophy]] between Devon and [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]], which Devon lost by 59 runs. The Maer has hosted 16 List A matches, the last of which came in the [[2005 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy]] when Devon hosted [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]]. In 2004 the ground played host to one of the biggest upsets in [[county cricket]] history when Devon defeated [[Leicestershire County Cricket Club|Leicestershire]] by losing fewer wickets in tying with Leicestershire's score of 156. In 2008, the ground played host to the touring [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]], who defeated Devon by ten runs in a one-day match.
==References== *[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/473.html The Maer Ground] on CricketArchive
